quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  11,63,"He said, \"O my people! Bethink you, if I stand upon a manifest sign (clear proof) from my Lord, and there come from Him mercy, who will help me against Allah if I rebel against Him? You will add to me naught but perdition"
  11,64,"O my people! This she-camel of Allah is a test (symbol, token) for you; leave her, then, to feed in AllahÂ´s earth, and touch her not with harm, lest a near torment seize you"
  11,65,"But they did hamstring her, and he said, \"Enjoy yourselves in your houses for three days; this is the promise that shall not be belied"
  11,66,"And when Our commandment came to pass, We saved Salih, and those who believed with him, by Our mercy, from the ignominy of that day. Verily, your Lord He is Powerful and Mighty"
  11,67,And a mighty noise caught those who had done wrong; and on the morrow they were lying corpses in their houses
  11,68,"As though they had never dwelt therein. Behold, Thamud indeed disbelieved in their Lord. Aye! Removed were the Thamud"
  11,69,"Our messengers came unto Abraham with Glad Tidings. They said, \"Peace!\" He answered, \"Peace be it!\" and did not delay to bring the roasted calf"
  11,70,"But when he saw that their hands reached not to it, he felt mistrust, and conceived a fear of them. They said, \"Fear not. Verily, we are sent unto the people of Lot"
  11,71,"And his wife was standing by, laughing; and We gave her the glad tidings of Isaac, and of Jacob after Isaac"